<h2>Welcome to Spludo</h2>

<p>
    This is your first spludo application. You may easily edit this page and
    create new ones. Getting started is easy, if you have a look at the
    tutorial over there at <a href="http://spludo.com">http://spludo.com</a>.
</p>


<h2>Edit this Application</h2>

<h3>Change the Contents</h3>
<p>
    If you want to change contents of this page, open
    <code>%%%project.name%%%/views/Homepage.ejs</code> and change it!
</p>

<h3>Change the Layout</h3>
<p>
    If you want to add additional stylesheets or any other stuff, which is same
    for most of the pages, you may want to alter the layout at
    <code>%%%project.name%%%/views/HtmlLayout.ejs</code>.
</p>

<h3>Change the URL</h3>
<p>
    If you want to change the url of that page, open
    <code>%%%project.name%%%/controllers/main-controllers.js</code> and change:
</p>
<pre>new Controller("", {</pre>
<p>
    to:
</p>
<pre>new Controller("hello-world", {</pre>
<p>
    Now you can open the page by using: <a href="/hello-world">/hello-world</a>
    instead of simple <a href="/">/</a>.
</p>

<h3>Change the CSS</h3>
<p>
    The used css file is available at
    <code>%%%project.name%%%/static/css/screen.css</code>.
</p>

<h2>Run in Console Mode</h2>
<p>
    If you want to launch the console mode, you can easily
    <code>node run_console.js shell.hello</code> in your
    <code>%%%project.name%%%/</code> folder.
</p>
<p>It should output something like this:</p>
<pre>$ node run_console.js shell.hello
Hello, back!</pre>

<h3>Edit Console Output</h3>

<p>
    Open <code>%%%project.name%%%/controllers/main-controllers.js</code> and
    change:
</p>
<pre>cb('Hello, back!');</pre>
<p>
    to:
</p>
<pre>cb('How are you?');</pre>

